Reference-contexts: To differentiate between perceptual and physical properties, I will use the word "edge" to denote the result of a processing stage on a single physical property, such as those found from normal "edge detection" techniques like the Canny operator <ref> [Can83] </ref>. The word "contour" will refer to the high-level perceptual feature that distinguishes between areas of similarity. <p> Both tasks will rely upon the same basic perceptual contour code with different back-end applications. We will use the physical characteristics from a Canny operator <ref> [Can83] </ref>, Guy and Medioni's point field detectors [GM94], a disparity estimator, and a textural processor. These edge detection methods will then by combined into a single contour identifier.
